SIMPLE: iodothyrin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iodothyrin
<hw>I`o*do*thy"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iodo-</ets> + <ets>thyro-</ets> + <ets>-in</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A peculiar substance obtained from the
thyroid gland, containing from nine to ten per cent of iodine.</def></p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is a very stable compound, and is believed to be
active principle in thyroid extracts and in the internal secretion of
the thyroid gland. It was originally called
<altname>thyroiodin</altname>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is probably an impure extract of thyroid gland,
containing thyroxine. See Merck Index 11th Ed. #9345, the entry for
thyroidin.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iodous</ent>⟦br⟧
